2026-04-11T18:19:16.6249870Z 
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6250040Z What to bundle, where to search:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6250620Z   --add-data SOURCE:DEST
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6251580Z                         Additional data files or directories containing data
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6254970Z                         files to be added to the application. The argument
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6256060Z                         value should be in form of "source:dest_dir", where
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6256540Z                         source is the path to file (or directory) to be
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6256860Z                         collected, dest_dir is the destination directory
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6257160Z                         relative to the top-level application directory, and
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6257530Z                         both paths are separated by a colon (:). To put a file
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6257840Z                         in the top-level application directory, use . as a
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6258130Z                         dest_dir. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6258370Z   --add-binary SOURCE:DEST
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6258600Z                         Additional binary files to be added to the executable.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6259470Z                         See the ``--add-data`` option for the format. This
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6259770Z                         option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6260110Z   -p DIR, --paths DIR   A path to search for imports (like using PYTHONPATH).
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6260440Z                         Multiple paths are allowed, separated by ``':'``, or
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6260810Z                         use this option multiple times. Equivalent to
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6261120Z                         supplying the ``pathex`` argument in the spec file.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6261430Z   --hidden-import MODULENAME, --hiddenimport MODULENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6261730Z                         Name an import not visible in the code of the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6262030Z                         script(s). This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6262320Z   --collect-submodules MODULENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6262580Z                         Collect all submodules from the specified package or
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6262900Z                         module. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6263200Z   --collect-data MODULENAME, --collect-datas MODULENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6263510Z                         Collect all data from the specified package or module.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6263810Z                         This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6264050Z   --collect-binaries MODULENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6264320Z                         Collect all binaries from the specified package or
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6264630Z                         module. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6264880Z   --collect-all MODULENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6265130Z                         Collect all submodules, data files, and binaries from
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6265450Z                         the specified package or module. This option can be
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6265730Z                         used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6265940Z   --copy-metadata PACKAGENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6266190Z                         Copy metadata for the specified package. This option
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6266470Z                         can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6266700Z   --recursive-copy-metadata PACKAGENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6266990Z                         Copy metadata for the specified package and all its
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6267300Z                         dependencies. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6267570Z   --additional-hooks-dir HOOKSPATH
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6267830Z                         An additional path to search for hooks. This option
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6268100Z                         can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6268320Z   --runtime-hook RUNTIME_HOOKS
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6268570Z                         Path to a custom runtime hook file. A runtime hook is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6269010Z                         code that is bundled with the executable and is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6269320Z                         executed before any other code or module to set up
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6269630Z                         special features of the runtime environment. This
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6269910Z                         option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6270140Z   --exclude-module EXCLUDES
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6270360Z                         Optional module or package (the Python name, not the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6270690Z                         path name) that will be ignored (as though it was not
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6270990Z                         found). This option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6271330Z   --splash IMAGE_FILE   (EXPERIMENTAL) Add an splash screen with the image
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6271690Z                         IMAGE_FILE to the application. The splash screen can
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6271980Z                         display progress updates while unpacking.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6272640Z 
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6272720Z How to generate:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6273450Z   -d {all,imports,bootloader,noarchive}, --debug {all,imports,bootloader,noarchive}
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6273860Z                         Provide assistance with debugging a frozen
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6274160Z                         application. This argument may be provided multiple
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6274460Z                         times to select several of the following options.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6274710Z                         
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6274920Z                         - all: All three of the following options.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6275160Z                         
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6275380Z                         - imports: specify the -v option to the underlying
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6275730Z                           Python interpreter, causing it to print a message
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6276040Z                           each time a module is initialized, showing the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6276350Z                           place (filename or built-in module) from which it
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6276630Z                           is loaded. See
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6276930Z                           https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#id4.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6277180Z                         
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6277400Z                         - bootloader: tell the bootloader to issue progress
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6277710Z                           messages while initializing and starting the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6278010Z                           bundled app. Used to diagnose problems with
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6278260Z                           missing imports.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6278450Z                         
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6278660Z                         - noarchive: instead of storing all frozen Python
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6278950Z                           source files as an archive inside the resulting
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6279250Z                           executable, store them as files in the resulting
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6279510Z                           output directory.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6279690Z                         
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6279940Z   --optimize LEVEL      Bytecode optimization level used for collected python
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6280300Z                         modules and scripts. For details, see the section
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6281240Z                         “Bytecode Optimization Level” in PyInstaller manual.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6281770Z   --python-option PYTHON_OPTION
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6282020Z                         Specify a command-line option to pass to the Python
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6282330Z                         interpreter at runtime. Currently supports "v"
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6282640Z                         (equivalent to "--debug imports"), "u", "W <warning
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6282950Z                         control>", "X <xoption>", and "hash_seed=<value>". For
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6283270Z                         details, see the section "Specifying Python
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6285140Z                         Interpreter Options" in PyInstaller manual.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6285970Z   -s, --strip           Apply a symbol-table strip to the executable and
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6286850Z                         shared libs (not recommended for Windows)
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6287140Z   --noupx               Do not use UPX even if it is available (works
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6287460Z                         differently between Windows and *nix)
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6287780Z   --upx-exclude FILE    Prevent a binary from being compressed when using upx.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6288200Z                         This is typically used if upx corrupts certain
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6288500Z                         binaries during compression. FILE is the filename of
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6288790Z                         the binary without path. This option can be used
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6289070Z                         multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6289200Z 
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6289290Z Windows and macOS specific options:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6289840Z   -c, --console, --nowindowed
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6290130Z                         Open a console window for standard i/o (default). On
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6290440Z                         Windows this option has no effect if the first script
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6290700Z                         is a '.pyw' file.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6290910Z   -w, --windowed, --noconsole
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6291170Z                         Windows and macOS: do not provide a console window for
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6291480Z                         standard i/o. On macOS this also triggers building a
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6291780Z                         macOS .app bundle. On Windows this option is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6292080Z                         automatically set if the first script is a '.pyw'
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6292430Z                         file. This option is ignored on *NIX systems.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6292760Z   --hide-console {minimize-early,hide-early,minimize-late,hide-late}
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6293090Z                         Windows only: in console-enabled executable, have
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6293400Z                         bootloader automatically hide or minimize the console
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6293720Z                         window if the program owns the console window (i.e.,
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6294160Z                         was not launched from an existing console window).
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6294620Z   -i <FILE.ico or FILE.exe,ID or FILE.icns or Image or "NONE">, --icon <FILE.ico or FILE.exe,ID or FILE.icns or Image or "NONE">
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6295090Z                         FILE.ico: apply the icon to a Windows executable.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6296660Z                         FILE.exe,ID: extract the icon with ID from an exe.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6297040Z                         FILE.icns: apply the icon to the .app bundle on macOS.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6297370Z                         If an image file is entered that isn't in the platform
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6297700Z                         format (ico on Windows, icns on Mac), PyInstaller
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6298020Z                         tries to use Pillow to translate the icon into the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6298320Z                         correct format (if Pillow is installed). Use "NONE" to
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6298640Z                         not apply any icon, thereby making the OS show some
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6298950Z                         default (default: apply PyInstaller's icon). This
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6299230Z                         option can be used multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6299480Z   --disable-windowed-traceback
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6299710Z                         Disable traceback dump of unhandled exception in
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6300020Z                         windowed (noconsole) mode (Windows and macOS only),
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6300320Z                         and instead display a message that this feature is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6300860Z                         disabled.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6300990Z 
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6301050Z Windows specific options:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6301280Z   --version-file FILE   Add a version resource from FILE to the exe.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6301550Z   --manifest <FILE or XML>
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6301740Z                         Add manifest FILE or XML to the exe.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6302010Z   -m <FILE or XML>      Deprecated shorthand for --manifest.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6302240Z   -r RESOURCE, --resource RESOURCE
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6302480Z                         Add or update a resource to a Windows executable. The
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6302750Z                         RESOURCE is one to four items,
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6303010Z                         FILE[,TYPE[,NAME[,LANGUAGE]]]. FILE can be a data file
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6303320Z                         or an exe/dll. For data files, at least TYPE and NAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6303630Z                         must be specified. LANGUAGE defaults to 0 or may be
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6304220Z                         specified as wildcard * to update all resources of the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6304530Z                         given TYPE and NAME. For exe/dll files, all resources
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6304840Z                         from FILE will be added/updated to the final
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6305120Z                         executable if TYPE, NAME and LANGUAGE are omitted or
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6305420Z                         specified as wildcard *. This option can be used
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6305670Z                         multiple times.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6305950Z   --uac-admin           Using this option creates a Manifest that will request
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6306260Z                         elevation upon application start.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6306560Z   --uac-uiaccess        Using this option allows an elevated application to
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6306880Z                         work with Remote Desktop.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6307030Z 
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6307090Z macOS specific options:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6307340Z   --argv-emulation      Enable argv emulation for macOS app bundles. If
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6307690Z                         enabled, the initial open document/URL event is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6307990Z                         processed by the bootloader and the passed file paths
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6308280Z                         or URLs are appended to sys.argv.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6308520Z   --osx-bundle-identifier BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6308800Z                         macOS .app bundle identifier is used as the default
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6309180Z                         unique program name for code signing purposes. The
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6309490Z                         usual form is a hierarchical name in reverse DNS
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6309750Z                         notation. For example:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6310020Z                         com.mycompany.department.appname (default: first
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6310340Z                         script's basename)
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6310560Z   --target-architecture ARCH, --target-arch ARCH
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6310860Z                         Target architecture (macOS only; valid values: x86_64,
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6311160Z                         arm64, universal2). Enables switching between
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6311450Z                         universal2 and single-arch version of frozen
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6311770Z                         application (provided python installation supports the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6312070Z                         target architecture). If not target architecture is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6312380Z                         not specified, the current running architecture is
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6312630Z                         targeted.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6312820Z   --codesign-identity IDENTITY
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6313050Z                         Code signing identity (macOS only). Use the provided
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6313520Z                         identity to sign collected binaries and generated
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6313820Z                         executable. If signing identity is not provided, ad-
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6314120Z                         hoc signing is performed instead.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6314350Z   --osx-entitlements-file FILENAME
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6314580Z                         Entitlements file to use when code-signing the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6314860Z                         collected binaries (macOS only).
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6315010Z 
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6315080Z Rarely used special options:
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6315240Z   --runtime-tmpdir PATH
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6315470Z                         Where to extract libraries and support files in
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6315770Z                         `onefile` mode. If this option is given, the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6316040Z                         bootloader will ignore any temp-folder location
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6316330Z                         defined by the run-time OS. The ``_MEIxxxxxx``-folder
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6316820Z                         will be created here. Please use this option only if
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6317130Z                         you know what you are doing. Note that on POSIX
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6317410Z                         systems, PyInstaller's bootloader does NOT perform
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6317710Z                         shell-style environment variable expansion on the
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6318000Z                         given path string. Therefore, using environment
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6318290Z                         variables (e.g., ``~`` or ``$HOME``) in path will NOT
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6318520Z                         work.
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6318700Z   --bootloader-ignore-signals
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6318930Z                         Tell the bootloader to ignore signals rather than
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6319210Z                         forwarding them to the child process. Useful in
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6319510Z                         situations where for example a supervisor process
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6319800Z                         signals both the bootloader and the child (e.g., via a
2026-04-11T18:19:16.6320100Z                         process group) to avoid signalling the child twice.
